Files that merely share a name no longer get grouped as duplicates when they are actually different photos. The scanner pairs same-stem files (e.g. a RAW+JPG or a Live Photo's video) by filename, which previously merged genuinely-unrelated files that collided on a name across merged folders, multiple cameras, or Google Takeout exports. Such a pair is now kept together only when their image content agrees (or one side is a video with no comparable hash), so a name collision no longer fabricates a duplicate group (#539).
